The paper deals with distributed algorithms for large-scale graph processing, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves sparsification techniques, which are commonly used in algorithms for sparse graphs and fall under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also introduces new algorithms for graph problems, which can be considered as a part of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with local computation algorithms, which can be considered as a part of Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
